text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild]]%0a%0a!Accent Discrimination in Education%0a%0a:Author: Simon_Y%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aSome of my thoughts on accent discrimination%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aLink to article:%0ahttps://www.theguardian.com/education/2020/oct/24/uk-top-universities-urged-act-classism-accent-prejudice%0a%0aIn this article, the Guardian investigation has found evidence of discriminatory acts against students with regional accents in some Russel group universities -- UK's counterpart to the Ivy League. Reports and interviews suggest that there is a "toxic" attitude towards students with a regional dialect/pronunciation, such as a northern England accent. The article also points out that this is not only discrimination against accents but also an instance of classism, where students are targets by their socio-economical background.%0a%0aWhile it is sad to believe that communities in Higher Education suffer from issues like this, it certainly exists. When I was in middle school, I participated in an exchange program to a well-reputed grammar school in the UK (a Grammar school in the UK is somewhat equivalent to a private school). Back then, I and some of my friends spoke English with a noticeable accent. By the end of the program, my classmates in the program who spoke with less accent blended into the host school's community much better. Some I have reasons to believe that discrimination does exist in prestigious institutions.%0a%0aAs a second language speaker of English, while I strive to speak the best Standard American English as I could, it is in all of our best interest to combat accent discrimination. After all, the linguistic background is part of your identity.%0a%0a%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a#foxbegin 210501-223232-810080#%0a(:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a!!!Additional example of discriminating against regional accents %0a-> - abbyl%0a(:div1end:) %0a>>messageitem%3c%3c %0aI found another example of discrimination in the UK against people speaking in regional accents in this reddit thread: https://www.reddit.com/r/AmItheAsshole/comments/iqsh5j/aita_for_telling_my_son_to_drop_his_fake/%0a%0aIn the thread, a parent complains that his young son started taking in a Yorkshire accent after moving to Yorkshire from Hampshire. The parent provides a few examples of his son's accent, saying that his son pronounces "right" as [ɹeɪt], "now" as [naɹ], and drops the [h] in words that contain the [h] sound. The parent concludes by saying he thinks the Yorkshire accent makes people unintelligent and that people with Yorkshire accents aren't taken seriously. As seen in the thread's comments, most people responded by saying that the parent was being extremely classist and snobby for his prescriptivism, which I completely agree with.%0a>>%3c%3c%0a#foxend 210501-223232-810080#%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a#foxbegin 210501-064558-209330#%0a(:div1 class=messagehead:)%0a>>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a[-30.04.2021 - 23:45-] &nbsp; %0a>>%3c%3c%0a(:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a>>rfloat%3c%3c%0a{[foxdelrange button 210501-064558-209330 {$FullName} ]}%0a>>%3c%3c%0a(:if1end:)%0a!!!!!Abi_S%0a(:div1end:) %0a>>messageitem%3c%3c %0a'''Language discrimination and power'''%0a>>messageitem%3c%3c%0aIt is pretty crazy to think language discrimination still occurs at elite schools, where you think those who speak the dominating language go. %0a>>%3c%3c%0a#foxend 210501-064558-209330#%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: A:)%0a(:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild:)
