diff:1619908352:1619851558:=54,64c54%0a%3c #foxbegin 210501-223232-810080#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Additional example of discriminating against regional accents %0a%3c -> - abbyl%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c I found another example of discrimination in the UK against people speaking in regional accents in this reddit thread: https://www.reddit.com/r/AmItheAsshole/comments/iqsh5j/aita_for_telling_my_son_to_drop_his_fake/%0a%3c %0a%3c In the thread, a parent complains that his young son started taking in a Yorkshire accent after moving to Yorkshire from Hampshire. The parent provides a few examples of his son's accent, saying that his son pronounces "right" as [ɹeɪt], "now" as [naɹ], and drops the [h] in words that contain the [h] sound. The parent concludes by saying he thinks the Yorkshire accent makes people unintelligent and that people with Yorkshire accents aren't taken seriously. As seen in the thread's comments, most people responded by saying that the parent was being extremely classist and snobby for his prescriptivism, which I completely agree with.%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 210501-223232-810080#%0a---%0a> %0a
